226
00:14:46,580 --> 00:14:51,083
Taro, today Mr. Maemura
was praising you.

227
00:14:52,055 --> 00:14:54,710
He said you've been opening up
about all sorts of things.

228
00:14:54,920 --> 00:14:56,836
The bad and the good.

229
00:14:58,932 --> 00:15:01,806
Mom, listen to this song later.
It's seriously amazing!

230
00:15:01,855 --> 00:15:05,087
Taro, I need you to listen
to what Mama's saying.

231
00:15:05,127 --> 00:15:09,123
Okay, I'm listening!
But you gotta watch it with me later, okay?

232
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:11,310
Let's watch it. Mama's excited too.

233
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:17,350
So, the things you tell Mr. Maemura,
try sharing some of that at home too, okay?

234
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:21,220
I don't really tell him anything.

235
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:24,420
Oh come on,
Counselor Maemura told me all about it.

236
00:15:25,692 --> 00:15:30,850
And Taro, if a girl says she doesn't
like that song, you stop, okay?

237
00:15:31,333 --> 00:15:35,470
It's not just girls. Some kids might
feel embarrassed and not like it either.

238
00:15:35,980 --> 00:15:41,110
And it's not just songs. When someone
says stop, you stop. That's important.

239
00:15:41,351 --> 00:15:43,838
I know. Daddy's the one
who doesn't stop.

240
00:15:43,917 --> 00:15:48,796
Right, Daddy. But you know, Daddy does stop
when Mama says she doesn't like something.

241
00:15:48,993 --> 00:15:52,910
That's right, Taro. Daddy doesn't do
things Mama says she doesn't like.

242
00:15:52,950 --> 00:15:54,267
Bullshit. You do it like crazy.

243
00:15:54,307 --> 00:15:55,904
You shouldn't say "like crazy."

244
00:15:55,944 --> 00:16:00,183
Oh right, Taro. Sorry.
Look at you being cool.

245
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:03,438
But Taro, if something bothers you,
make sure you say so, okay?

246
00:16:03,478 --> 00:16:05,160
Of course I do.

247
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:06,413
- Got it?
- Yeah.

248
00:16:06,666 --> 00:16:08,245
I do say it. I really do.

249
00:16:08,285 --> 00:16:10,916
- Really?
- Really! I say it like crazy.

250
00:16:14,624 --> 00:16:18,223
Okay, it's past 8:30. Time's up.

251
00:16:18,718 --> 00:16:20,830
Mama's taking a bath,
so go to bed with Daddy.

252
00:16:20,870 --> 00:16:22,310
Five more minutes.

253
00:16:22,350 --> 00:16:25,528
What are you saying? I already gave you
an extra ten minutes today.

254
00:16:25,710 --> 00:16:27,676
I'll come to bed right away today.

255
00:16:28,511 --> 00:16:31,330
Promise! Make sure you come
before I fall asleep.

256
00:16:31,350 --> 00:16:32,552
I promise.

257
00:16:32,819 --> 00:16:34,096
Good night.

258
00:16:34,983 --> 00:16:40,463
I have to stop that from happening.
I need to get Taro to sleep ASAP tonight.

259
00:16:41,183 --> 00:16:47,016
Okay, Taro! Brush your teeth.
Come on, bedtime. Nighty-night.

260
00:16:47,687 --> 00:16:49,223
No iPad.

261
00:16:50,999 --> 00:16:56,430
"We searched for the rock connecting
Tangerina Island and Animal Island."

262
00:16:56,918 --> 00:16:58,665
Come on, Taro. Go to sleep.

263
00:17:00,010 --> 00:17:01,590
I'm not sleepy yet.

264
00:17:01,630 --> 00:17:05,871
You're going to sleep. Close your eyes
and listen, and you'll drift off.

265
00:17:05,918 --> 00:17:10,417
Daddy, watch Doburock too.
Mama watches it with me.

266
00:17:10,457 --> 00:17:13,270
Okay, I will. Daddy likes
Doburock too, you know.

267
00:17:13,310 --> 00:17:14,590
Really? Let's watch now!

268
00:17:16,154 --> 00:17:17,367
You'll sleep after?

269
00:17:17,414 --> 00:17:19,630
Fine, I'll sleep. If I have to.

270
00:17:20,331 --> 00:17:22,536
Okay. But just that one, deal?

271
00:17:22,652 --> 00:17:25,396
Don't tell Mama, okay? Promise.

272
00:17:30,930 --> 00:17:32,490
Lie down, lie down.

273
00:17:49,091 --> 00:17:52,430
Could it be, could it be,
could it be...

274
00:18:19,106 --> 00:18:22,490
I told you not to come in
while I'm in the damn bath.

275
00:18:22,825 --> 00:18:25,930
Sorry. I thought you were
getting out soon.

276
00:18:25,970 --> 00:18:27,570
So what if I was?

277
00:18:30,505 --> 00:18:32,730
Standing there like that
is seriously intimidating.

278
00:18:33,398 --> 00:18:38,640
Um, sorry. So, uh...
did you read my message?

279
00:18:38,917 --> 00:18:40,124
What message?

280
00:18:40,214 --> 00:18:41,953
Oh, well, um...

281
00:18:43,424 --> 00:18:46,666
Oh, that shitty message.
No. I don't want to.

282
00:18:47,045 --> 00:18:49,676
Huh? Why not?

283
00:18:49,969 --> 00:18:52,309
Because I don't want to,
obviously.

284
00:18:52,630 --> 00:18:56,970
And don't send me that crap
during work. Totally killed my mood.

285
00:18:57,323 --> 00:19:04,130
I'm sorry. But I just don't know
how to ask you anymore.

286
00:19:05,329 --> 00:19:10,591
What are you even so unhappy about?
Sure, I don't earn much, but...

287
00:19:10,631 --> 00:19:12,070
"A little"? Try a lot.

288
00:19:12,776 --> 00:19:14,283
Okay, a lot less, but...

289
00:19:14,403 --> 00:19:20,312
I make up for it with childcare
and housework, more than most dads.

290
00:19:20,469 --> 00:19:25,910
The fact you even say that pisses me off.
Housework and childcare are a given.

291
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:29,823
And compare yourself to me,
not other dads.

292
00:19:30,376 --> 00:19:36,430
Plus you never handle the annoying stuff
like school forms or therapy paperwork.

293
00:19:36,795 --> 00:19:40,690
Cooking is the one thing you can do
because you're such a damn glutton.

294
00:19:40,730 --> 00:19:43,753
Like that's anywhere near enough
to make me want to have sex.

295
00:19:43,793 --> 00:19:45,629
It's not just cooking, though.

296
00:19:45,669 --> 00:19:51,375
Can't you at least acknowledge my efforts
a little? I mean, I'll try harder, but...

297
00:19:51,415 --> 00:19:53,216
And who acknowledges MY efforts?

298
00:19:53,723 --> 00:19:55,230
I do.

299
00:19:55,303 --> 00:20:00,356
I don't need YOUR approval. And you're
putting your effort in all wrong anyway.

300
00:20:00,530 --> 00:20:01,734
How so?

301
00:20:01,996 --> 00:20:03,876
Figure it out yourself.

302
00:20:04,257 --> 00:20:11,303
Look, I'll try harder
at all kinds of stuff, so...

303
00:20:15,258 --> 00:20:19,250
So a wife can't even say no
to having sex with her husband?

304
00:20:19,535 --> 00:20:22,672
That's not what I'm saying.
You turn me down all the time anyway.

305
00:20:22,936 --> 00:20:27,010
Well by that logic, can't a husband
even ask his wife for sex?

306
00:20:27,050 --> 00:20:28,890
You do it constantly, asshole.

307
00:20:28,930 --> 00:20:32,850
Yeah, but if even asking
isn't allowed, then that's basically...

308
00:20:33,064 --> 00:20:36,348
power harassment or emotional abuse
or something, isn't it?

309
00:20:36,430 --> 00:20:40,670
Huh? How is that harassment?
What an incredible quote.

310
00:20:40,710 --> 00:20:42,005
I should tell everyone in Japan.

311
00:20:42,045 --> 00:20:45,599
I'm just saying, maybe consider
my feelings a little...

312
00:20:45,639 --> 00:20:48,350
You're not considering
MY feelings either.

313
00:20:48,390 --> 00:20:55,470
But then... what am I
supposed to do?

314
00:20:56,758 --> 00:21:00,893
Ugh, this is such a pain in the ass.

315
00:21:02,780 --> 00:21:09,489
Fine, just do it. You're not gonna back off
till I let you anyway, right? God.

316
00:21:09,626 --> 00:21:11,950
Just so you know,
this is basically rape.

317
00:21:12,081 --> 00:21:13,870
If I called the cops,
you'd be arrested.

318
00:21:13,910 --> 00:21:15,678
No, come on...

319
00:21:16,039 --> 00:21:19,345
Just hurry up and do it.
I wanna get back to my show.

320
00:21:19,396 --> 00:21:22,216
Okay. I'll go get the futon.

321
00:21:29,061 --> 00:21:32,386
Here we go... there...

322
00:21:35,516 --> 00:21:36,729
Excuse me.

323
00:21:44,415 --> 00:21:46,263
The futon's ready.

324
00:22:14,663 --> 00:22:15,665
Next Episode Preview

325
00:22:15,705 --> 00:22:18,145
You don't understand marital
consent at all, do you?

326
00:22:18,185 --> 00:22:19,194
I do understand.

327
00:22:19,234 --> 00:22:23,880
Life's so boring.
No one to even cheat with.

328
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:27,025
The bad guy is you, Daddy.
Stop talking to me.

329
00:22:27,160 --> 00:22:29,240
Why are we so stupid?
